### 7. **No Token Revocation on Logout/Cleanup**

**Location:** `dispose()` (lines 376-378)  
**Risk:** MEDIUM - Zombie tokens, security compliance issues

**Issue:** The `dispose()` method is a no-op. Tokens should be revoked when the client is disposed to prevent unauthorized access.

**Recommended Fix:**
```typescript
/**
 * Revoke OAuth2 tokens and cleanup resources
 */
async dispose(): Promise<void> {
  try {
    // Revoke tokens with Google
    if (this.auth.credentials.access_token) {
      await this.auth.revokeCredentials();
      console.log('[GmailClient] OAuth2 tokens revoked successfully');
    }

    // Clear from secure storage if configured
    if (this.tokenStorage && this.currentUserId) {
      await this.tokenStorage.revokeTokens(this.currentUserId);
    }

    // Clear in-memory credentials
    this.auth.setCredentials({});
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[GmailClient] Error during cleanup:', error);
    // Don't throw - cleanup should be best-effort
  }
}
```

